DC  Nucleotide excision repair
DR  KEGG; map03420;
CC  The XPC complex recognizes damaged DNA which is required for 
CC  global genome nucleotide excision repair [1]. Once XPC 
CC  has interacted with unpaired bases on the undamaged DNA strand, 
CC  the TFIH complex is recruited to find lesions on the opposite 
CC  strand. The XPC complex is composed of XPC, RAD23B and CETN2 
CC  [2].
**  Evidence for step 3 is also used in GP2042 and GP2045.
